    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Breach at Los Alamos: Who'll Take the Blame?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brian Reynolds letter finds it appalling that he is taped by surveillance cameras at ATMs while 'more than two dozen' people have unfettered access to Los Alamos vault containing nation's nuclear secrets (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lost at Los Alamos'' (editorial, June 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lost at Los Alamos'' (editorial, June 15):</p>
        <p>You correctly raise many serious concerns about the most recent security breach at the Los Alamos National Laboratory. I find it appalling that I cannot enter a local bank and remove $20 from an automated teller machine without being taped, yet ''more than two dozen'' people have unfettered access to a vault that holds this country's nuclear secrets.</p>
        <p>BRIAN REYNOLDS  Piscataway, N.J., June 15, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
